
[1]hint

   HINT, v.t. To bring to mind by a slight mention or remote allusion; to
   allude to; to suggest by a slight intimation.

   Just hint a fault, and hesitate dislike.

        HINT, v.i. To hint at, is to allude to; to mention slightly.

   HINT, n. A distant allusion; slight mention; intimation; insinuation; a
   word or two intended to give notice, or remind one of something without
                     a full declaration or explanation.

   1. Suggestion.
